The paper deals with the estimation of channel coefficients and frequency offsets for MIMO systems, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes methods to exploit the structure of the channel matrix, which can be seen as a system-level approach and thus falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed methods, which involves statistical analysis and modeling, making it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
